## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- CMake (version >= 3.10)
- A modern C++ compiler with support for C++17 (GCC, Clang, etc.)
- Eigen library

### Compiling LSQUANT

To compile LSQUANT, follow these steps:

```bash
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../toolchain-gcc.cmake ..
cmake --build .
